<div class="postright">
<h3>TUTORIAL: Login screen with slim</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>#Install #mod #login<br/>1. Why slim? Why not ligthdm, or something else?<br/>I am not a pro-guy, so I can not tell you about technology of these application. I can not edit source code or optimize lightdm too, and slim give me everything I need: simple configuration, no dialog box, and it is on repo. So, here we go!</p><p>2. What do you need to do?<br/>a) First of all, install slim</p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>sudo apt install slim</code></pre></div><p>Installation should ask you the default Desktop Manager, choose slim instead of lightdm<br/>b)<br/>*) Download my theme. Links:</p><div class="codebox"><pre><code> https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B5V6NPBa8YBSdnpQLXlPRjB2SEU/view </code></pre></div><p>Mirror link:</p><div class="codebox"><pre><code> https://mega.nz/#!KUhiESTR!3jjaDc-GoN_dxtfwUyk1hmohm7I5uEOVYIUhmzZrd0k </code></pre></div><p>*) Install my theme: put my folder in </p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>/usr/share/slim/themes/</code></pre></div><p>*) Edit </p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>/etc/slim.conf </code></pre></div><p>Find ‘current_theme’ and set the theme name (name of the folder - no need full path)<br/>ex: </p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>current_theme	&lt;my_slim&gt;</code></pre></div><p>I am very sorry. My tutorial was not very clear for newbie. Theme&#039;s name is folder&#039;s name in </p><div class="codebox"><pre><code> /usr/share/slim/themes/ </code></pre></div><p> and you have to change &lt;my_slim&gt; to theme&#039;s name (folder&#039;s name)<br/>c) What do you need to know?<br/>*) Slim configration file at /etc/slim.conf → you need to edit this file to choose your theme<br/>*) Slim theme folder at /usr/share/slim/themes/ → My theme should be stored here<br/>*) Slim theme configuration /usr/share/slim/themes/&lt;theme_name&gt;/slim.theme → customize your theme<br/>*) Theme background and dialog box in image format (png)in the same folder<br/>*) Slim wiki, read everything about slim at </p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/SLiM</code></pre></div><p>3. Optional install slimlock and use slim as your screensaver<br/>*) Download slimlock source code at </p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>https://github.com/joelburget/slimlock</code></pre></div><p>*) Install lib: </p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>sudo apt install libimlib2-dev libxft-dev libpam0g-dev</code></pre></div><p>*) Install slimlock (Read README for more information)<br/>*) After installing successful, go to your control center → keyboard shortcut → add → command ‘/usr/share/slimlock’ and set hotkey (example: ctr + alt + l)<br/>*) Should I remove lightdm and mate-screensaver? I can not sure, but I still remove them.<br/>4. Because of some reasons, I use parrot background as theme background, but you can still choose your own background, nsa background is in the folder too<br/><a href="https://postimg.org/image/ddgosbgyb/" rel="nofollow"><span class="postimg"><img src="https://s21.postimg.org/ddgosbgyb/Screenshot_at_2017-05-25_13-55-12.png" alt="Screenshot_at_2017-05-25_13-55-12.png"/></span></a></p>
<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by dmknght (2017-05-27 16:48:33)</em></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
