<h3>Re: TUTORIAL: Login screen with slim</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<div class="quotebox"><cite>brianeli22 wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><div class="quotebox"><cite>josegatica wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><div class="quotebox"><cite>brianeli22 wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>My OS was error when I installing Slim, cannot login with my user, but when I login with ROOT user it worked, but some app and driver not working. Can you help me how to fix that?</p></div></blockquote></div><p>your system shouldn&#039;t show any error. Did you read all the post? or just copied and pasted commands.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>&quot;Failed to execute login command&quot; when I login with default user. And when I try to login with root. Its works. <br/>I try to find how to fix it, I will post new thread to sharing with other who got same problem :)</p></div></blockquote></div><p>You did not post all of steps that you did, so there is many reason that i can think about:<br/>1) Your OS version?<br/>2) Have you installed slim in the right way?<br/>3) Have you named them right? A wrong name can crash your Desktop Manager<br/>4) If log in as root work, maybe your system set wrong permission? With loggin as root user, applications and drivers can not work right, many functions are disabled<br/>5) Have you installed any desktop environment, or desktop management that can disable slim?<br/>6) Have you removed any keyring, or anything that can make authentication work wrong?</p>
