<div class="postmsg">
<div class="quotebox"><cite>dmknght wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><div class="quotebox"><cite>brianeli22 wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><div class="quotebox"><cite>josegatica wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>your system shouldn&#039;t show any error. Did you read all the post? or just copied and pasted commands.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>&quot;Failed to execute login command&quot; when I login with default user. And when I try to login with root. Its works. <br/>I try to find how to fix it, I will post new thread to sharing with other who got same problem :)</p></div></blockquote></div><p>You did not post all of steps that you did, so there is many reason that i can think about:<br/>1) Your OS version?<br/>2) Have you installed slim in the right way?<br/>3) Have you named them right? A wrong name can crash your Desktop Manager<br/>4) If log in as root work, maybe your system set wrong permission? With loggin as root user, applications and drivers can not work right, many functions are disabled<br/>5) Have you installed any desktop environment, or desktop management that can disable slim?<br/>6) Have you removed any keyring, or anything that can make authentication work wrong?</p></div></blockquote></div><p>1) My OS version is 3.6.<br/>2) Yes bro<br/>3) Yes named slim on theme folder<br/>4) That&#039;s what I&#039;m experiencing now, and I&#039;m trying to find my fault when install SLIM<br/>5) No I don&#039;t have any desktop enviroment, just install slim<br/>6) I don&#039;t remove any keyring, And I will find the error ASAP then Posting here where is my fault</p><p>Thanks for your help, I appreciate it :) Keep sharing with other Parrot User :)</p>
